 Obtain User Consent
 
Description: Obtain user consent for data collection and storage in compliance with GDPR regulations.

Goals: 
   - Ensure that user data is collected and stored with user consent and in compliance with GDPR regulations.
   - Provide users with a clear option to opt-in or opt-out of data collection.

Scope: This initiative will involve implementing a consent form that clearly communicates data collection practices and gives users the option to opt-in or opt-out of data collection.

Outcomes:

   - Compliance with GDPR regulations.
   - Improved user trust and confidence.

Deliverables:

   - Consent form created and implemented.
   - User data collection practices updated to comply with consent form.

Milestones:

   - Consent form created and reviewed by legal team (Week 1).
   - Consent form implemented on the website (Week 2).
   - User data collection practices updated to comply with consent form (Week 3).

Constraints: Limited user participation in consent forms.

Assumptions: Users will understand the data collection practices outlined in the consent form.

Risks:

   - Non-compliance with GDPR regulations.
   - User mistrust and reduced engagement due to privacy concerns.

Dependencies: Legal team review and approval.

Team: Legal Counsel (Lead), Web Developer, Project Manager.

